<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915473>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2. Original illustrations accompanying the description of Thespoides bolivari Chopard, 1916 (original numbering and captions included). The full specimen is depicted on the left (notice the absence of cursorial legs, which were missing at the time of description), whereas on the right there is a dorsal view of the last abdominal segments (including supraanal plate and cerci), distal inner lobe of the fore coxa and trochanter. Not to scale." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4915473/files/figure.png" .

